cleaned_text: Veterinary Biological Products Licensees and Permittees Prepared February 2 , 2023 United States Department of Agriculture Marketing and Regulatory Programs Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service Veterinary Services Center for Veterinary Biologics 1920 Dayton Avenue Ames, IA 50010 PHONE (515) 337- 6100 FAX (515) 337- 6120 INTRODUCTION This quarterly publication lists all licensed establishments, licensees, and permittees, with their subsidiaries and divisions, as well as the biological products they are authorized to produce or import. An alphabetical listing identifies the firms with the appropriate establishment license number. The listing of licensed establishments by number identifies each licensee, permittee, subsidiary, and division authorized to do business in the establishment. The index of product components lists by page number where each antigenic fraction appears. The fraction reference may appear in more than one section, for example, canine distemper appears in vaccines, antiserums, vaccines with bacterin-toxoids, and diagnostics. Under the alphabetical listing of licensed biological products, the principal parts of the true name are underlined, and each product is assigned a code number by Policy, Evaluation, and Licensing. A separate license is issued and a code number assigned for each Outline of Production filed. The license number of each firm authorized to produce a biological product is listed to the right of the product. The alphanumeric system used for product codes provides for a six-digit number of number-letter combination to be assigned to each product, i.e., the first digit denotes product types; second and third, group by agents; fourth, the viability of vaccine, (live, killed, modified live, etc.); fifth, substrates; and sixth, miscellaneous variables. Included in this issue is a section designated "Products for Further Manufacture." These products represent one or more biological fractions brought to a prescribed stage of production requiring further processing before becoming a completed or finished product. True names for these products describe only the product licensed, such as virus, killed culture, purified antibody, etc. Current product nomenclature such as vaccine, bacterin, etc., will be used only for completed product. Errors in this document or suggestions for improvement should be brought to the attention of: USDA, APHIS, VS Center for Veterinary Biologics Policy, Evaluation, and Licensing 1920 Dayton Ave, PO Box 844 Ames, IA 50010 For on-line information, the Internet address is https://www.aphis.usda.gov/aphis/ourfocus/animalhealth/veterinary-biologics.
